      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The validated QoI must be the absolute normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) directly used for clinical threshold comparison, not a surrogate such as shear stress or power consumption.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the primary QoI and is directly compared to the clinical threshold. However, the hemolysis model was calibrated on a different pump geometry and the transfer of calibration constants introduces unquantified model-form uncertainty. Achieved level 3 against required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
