      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must be conducted on the same device geometry, at the same operating conditions, and with blood or a validated blood analog at physiological hematocrit.",
      "rationale": "Validation used water-glycerol analog at non-physiological viscosity; hematocrit effects on hemolysis are not captured. Geometry is the FDA generic pump, which approximates but does not replicate the clinical VAD geometry. Achieved level 2 against required level 5."
